SIMPLE: tonometer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonometer
<hw>To*nom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
stretching, a tone + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physics.)</fld> <def>An instrument for determining the rate of
vibrations in tones.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An apparatus for
studying and registering the action of various fluids and drugs on the
excised heart of lower animals.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An instrument
for measuring tension, esp. that of the eyeball.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tonometry</ent>⟦br⟧
